## Introduction to Linux

### What is Linux?

Linux is an open-source operating system based on the Unix operating system. It is widely used in servers, cloud infrastructure, networking equipment, embedded systems, and cybersecurity environments.

### Why Linux is Important

* Open-source and free to use
* Highly customizable
* Secure and stable
* Widely used in cybersecurity and ethical hacking
* Powers a large portion of the internet and cloud services

### Origins of Linux

Linux was created by Linus Torvalds in 1991.

The Linux kernel became the foundation for many Linux distributions, including:

* Ubuntu
* Debian
* Fedora
* Kali Linux
* Arch Linux

